Description:
Apologies if I am doing something wrong - I am still very new to Verilator.
When attempting to verilate a pretty simple module that uses a clocking block, I get an internal fault error.
Commenting out the clocking block fixes the issue and I am able to proceed.
Example file test.sv
module tb();
    logic clk = 0;
    logic x;
    logic y;

    always #1ns clk = ~clk;

    clocking cb @(posedge clk);
        output #1ns x;
        input #1step y;
    endclocking

    initial begin
        repeat(10) @(posedge clk);
        $finish();
    end
endmodule
Command-line & error
$ ./verilator/bin/verilator --sv --binary  test.sv 
%Error: Verilator internal fault, sorry. Suggest trying --debug --gdbbt
%Error: Command Failed ulimit -s unlimited 2>/dev/null; exec /home/alex/test_verilator/verilator/bin/verilator_bin --sv --binary test.sv
Version & OS
I tried on both:

Verilator 5.017 devel rev v5.014-213-g7b12f6a1d
Verilator 5.016 2023-09-16 rev v5.014-149-g57c816f90

Ubuntu 22.04
